result.execSummary:
The defendant Lakendra M Wilson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Neglecting a Child, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 948.21(1)(a).
  • Neglecting a Child, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 948.21(1)(a).
  • Neglecting a Child, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 948.21(1)(a).
  • Neglecting a Child, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 948.21(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

records.addlTxt:
Sentencing Proceeded. Statements by parties and defendant.

AS TO COUNT 2:
The court sentenced the defendant to 60 DAYS in the House of Correction, with credit for 42 DAYS time served. Court ordered defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.
 The court orders defendant to pay all applicable costs, fees, assessments and surcharges as a condition of probation as imposed in counts 3, 4, and 5, and failure to do so will result in entry of civil judgment.


AS TO COUNT 3:
The court sentenced the defendant to 5 MONTHS in the House of Correction, consecutive to count 4 and 5.  Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 24 MONTHS, concurrent.

AS TO COUNT 4:
The court sentenced the defendant to 5 MONTHS in the House of Correction, consecutive to count 3 and 5.  Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 24 MONTHS, concurrent.

AS TO COUNT 5:
The court sentenced the defendant to 5 MONTHS in the House of Correction, consecutive to count 3 and 4.  Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 24 MONTHS, concurrent.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION FOR COUNTS 3, 4 AND 5:
-Comply with CPS orders and any other Court orders
-Parenting classes.
-Mental health evaluation, comply with recommended treatment.
-AODA assessment, comply with recommended treatment.
-Treatment and/or counseling as determined by agent.
-Obtain/maintain employment.
-Pay all MANDATORY court costs, fees, and surcharges including: DNA & DV surcharges during period of probation for counts 3, 4, 5 and also count 2, failure to pay will result in a civil judgment. 
-Provide DNA sample.


Counsel to notify defendant of right to seek post conviction relief.

Defendant Lakendra M Wilson in court with attorney Annamarie Amy Wineke.  Molly M Schmidt appeared for the State of Wisconsin. BRANCH 38 FOR BRANCH 21. Parties have reached a resolution.

AS TO COUNT 1: Pursuant to plea negotiation, on states motion, Court orders COUNT 1 IS DISMISSED BUT READ IN.

AS TO COUNT 2, 3, 4,  AND 5:
Defendant changes her plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived her rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.
JusticePoint Pretrial Services Report received and filed.
JusticePoint Violation Report received and filed. Court will address at next court date.
